// scenarios/67-jenkins-grab-sandbox-bypass
// CICD-SEC-4 (Poisoned Pipeline Execution) — Jenkins
//
// Pattern: an AST-transforming annotation (`@Grab`) in a Jenkinsfile / sandboxed
// shared library. `@Grab` is applied during *compilation*, BEFORE the Groovy
// sandbox's runtime checks, so a user who controls a Jenkinsfile or sandboxed
// library can fetch and execute arbitrary Java on the controller — a full
// sandbox bypass / RCE. This is the CVE-2019-1003000 / -1003001 / -1003002
// (SECURITY-1266) class; public PoCs grab `org.buildobjects:jproc` and run shell.
//
// SAFETY: static fixture, nested under scenarios/ — Jenkins only runs a
// Jenkinsfile a job is explicitly configured to load; nothing here configures
// one. See README.md.

@Grab(group = 'org.buildobjects', module = 'jproc', version = '2.8.2')
import org.buildobjects.process.ProcBuilder

pipeline {
    agent { label 'build-linux' }
    stages {
        stage('Build') {
            steps {
                // The danger is the compile-time @Grab above; by the time any
                // step runs, arbitrary Java has already been pulled and loaded.
                echo 'built'
            }
        }
    }
}
